kill — send a signal to a process

SYNOPSIS
  kill [-9 | -KILL | -TERM] PID...

DESCRIPTION
  Default sends SIGTERM, a cooperative shutdown request. Targets that
  subscribe to ipc "proc.term" can clean up; targets sleeping in
  sched.wait are woken via the synthetic "__sigterm__<pid>" signal.

  -9 (SIGKILL) is destructive: the proc record is disposed immediately
  and proc.exit is published with code = -9. The Lua coroutine is left
  for the GC to reap (Lua has no coroutine.throw).

  Both signal forms require the syscall:kill capability when cap
  enforcement is on. With enforce=false the audit log records the
  intent but the kill proceeds.

EXAMPLES
  ps                  list running processes
  kill 7              ask pid 7 to terminate
  kill -9 12          force-kill pid 12

SEE ALSO
  ps(1), svc(1)
